

=Description=

"GeneralAssembly.Us is an online platform for direct democracy. Here you can join your community, city, state, and national assemblies in organizing at the grass roots level. Proposals can be made and voted upon, allowing the people in your assembly to join together for your common good. Plan a dance, start a coop business, or organize a protest... it's all about people power!

‎GeneralAssembly.Us is being built to take advantage of modern computer networking to provide a framework upon which to build [[Dual Power]] institutions. There is currently the ability to make and vote upon proposals. Soon there will also be a work exchange which will provide a people engine to further our common goals, as well as provide a means to employ each other when the monetary-based "business cycle" fails (.Us)."
(http://generalassembly.us/)


